nd the ricotta can drain freely."},{"content":"Transfer drained ricotta (approx. 250 g, depending on time left to drain) into a bowl and set aside."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Dumplings"},{"content":"Place bread, Parmesan, lemon zest, basil, oregano and salt into mixing bowl and mill <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>."},{"content":"Add reserved ricotta and combine <b>15 sec\/speed 3<b>, to form a crumbly mixture."},{"content":"Grease Varoma tray with oil. Then, using wet hands, squeeze ricotta mixture into walnut-sized balls to form dumplings and place dumplings onto greased Varoma tray. Set Varoma aside."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Napoli sauce"},{"content":"Place onion and garlic into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add oil and sauté <b>3 min 30 sec\/120°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add all remaining sauce ingredients and cook <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Place Varoma with dumplings into position, secure lid and cook <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Place dumplings and sauce into shallow bowls, sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and garnish with extra basil leaves. Serve hot."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","If you don't have a nut milk bag or muslin cloth, you can line your simmering basket using paper towel instead in step 3."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","55m","4 portions"]}